'{"A": "walking", "B": "ordinary", "C": "dangerous", "D": "formal"}',
'B',
'{"rationale": "Pedestrian as an adjective means ordinary or unimaginative. The context of lacking creativity, following predictable patterns, and being unremarkable all support this meaning of commonplace or dull.", "why_others_wrong": {"A": "Pedestrian as noun means walker, but used as adjective here", "C": "No connection to danger in literary criticism context", "D": "Formality is not discussed; issue is lack of creativity"}}',
ARRAY['word-meaning', 'literary-criticism', 'secondary-meanings']),

('Craft & Structure', 'mcq', 'hard',
